Alassa ( 34 ° 46 N, 32 ° 55 EW) is located at 322 meters a.s.l. in the Troodos region. The specimens were live­trapped in abandoned cultivation terraces colonised by Thorny Broom (
Calycotome villosa
), Thorny Gorse (
Genista sphacelata
), Rock­Rose (
Cistus creticus and C. salviifolius
), Asphodel (
Asphodelus aestivus
) and shrubs such as Mastic trees, or Lentisks
( Pistacia lentiscus )
and grasses (Avena sp. oats).

